These fabrics are analyzed, processed and frozen before being stored in Hema-Québec, which also manages the only public bank of cordon blood in Quebec.
The umbilical cord that was previously considered a biomedical waste is a blood rich in stem cells that can be used to treat serious diseases, such as leukaemia.
