Open Office has paid particular attention to the interaction with Office 2007 suite, and it is indeed possible to open the documents with the new extension of Microsoft (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx.)
Also interesting, certain functions specific to some modules, such as that that that allows to reduce the dimensions of PowerPoint presentations, useful for example, to send them by e-mail, or to import PDF files into the graphical development module, keeping the original aspect of the page.
Also on this front, it is possible to create documents (PDF hybrids) that connect the typical Adobe-format chart to the elements of a spreadsheet or text maker.
Collaboration between several people is an element that has had various improvements within applications: in the spreadsheet, various users can intervene, avoiding conflicts about changes, in the drafting of texts, as each contributor is given a colour of comments for better recognition in the revision phase.
Some companies are even working to bring certain functions of OpenOffice on the Web (on the cloud, on the cloud), and in the next few weeks, they should deliver the final result.
