Kohl is also positive, it is the fourth case of doping.
New case of positivity in the last Tour de France: it is the Austrian of the Gerolsteiner team, Bernhard Kohl, qualified third, and winner of the jersey of the best climber.
This is the website of the daily L'Equipe that reports the news.
At 26 years of age, Kohl is the fourth positive cyclist in the Cera, the third-generation Epo, after the Italian Riccò and Leonardo Piepoli, and German Stefan Schumacher, also from Gerolsteiner.
The blood tests performed on the Kohl test are part of those carried out in recent weeks by the laboratories of Lausanne and Chatenay-Malabry.
If counter-analysis confirms the positivity in the Cera, the Austrian will lose its third place in the Tour and will have to expect two years of elimination.
The news of Kohl's positivity at the third generation Epo was confirmed by the chief of the French anti-doping agency, Pierre Bordry, who communicated to the Associated Press, having notified the positivity to the Austrian authorities.
The 26-year-old Austrian stood on the podium behind the Spanish Carlos Sastre and the American Cadel Evans, thus radiating the best climber's pole jersey.
